Introduction

Pedicab drivers in Dumaguete City make numerous decisions every day, such as choosing which passenger to pick up, selecting appropriate routes and deciding how long to work. Continuously making these decisions for extended periods can lead to mental exhaustion, commonly known as decision fatigue.

When pedicab drivers experience decision fatigue, they may become stressed and confused. These conditions can negatively affect their safety, health, and daily income, and may also affect commuters. Because of this, there is a need for a system that can help reduce mental exhaustion and support better decision-making among pedicab drivers.

The Pedicab Driver Decision Fatigue System is developed to assist pedicab drivers in Dumaguete City by providing simple and clear guidance. The system includes a virtual map feature that shows the availability of commuters in specific areas and the routes that the pedicab driver will pass through. This helps drivers decide where to go next without confusion or unnecessary overthinking. The system also benefits the commuters particularly students by making transportation easier and faster, especially for those living in secluded or hard-to-reach areas. By helping drivers choose better routes and stay focused, the system ensures that they can reach their destinations more quickly, safely, and conveniently while improving the overall reliability of pedicab services within the city.

Name of the Specific Establishment
The system will be implemented under the Traffic Management Office (TMO) of Dumaguete City for pedicab drivers operating within Dumaguete City. The proposed system is called the Pedicab Driver Decision Fatigue Support System. It is specifically designed for local pedicab drivers who provide daily transportation services throughout the city.
The system focuses on small-scale and community-based pedicab operations in Dumaguete City, where drivers often work long hours and rely heavily on personal judgment when making daily work-related decisions. Through the support of the TMO, the system aims to promote safer, more organized, and more efficient pedicab operations within the city.

