Scope and Limitations

 	The Pedicab Driver Decision Fatigue Support System is designed to assist pedicab drivers in Dumaguete City by providing guidance on passenger availability, optimal routes, and work-rest schedules to reduce decision fatigue. The system is mobile-based for drivers and commuters, particularly students, and includes a web-based platform for the Traffic Management Office (TMO) to monitor operations. Its implementation focuses on small-scale, community-based pedicab services, covering main roads, residential areas, and secluded locations within the city. Limitations of the system include reliance on mobile devices and internet connectivity, potential inaccuracies in passenger requests or location data, and the fact that it is only applicable within Dumaguete City. The system’s effectiveness is also limited by user adoption and the drivers’ willingness to follow the suggested routes and recommendations.

Objectives
•	To reduce mental fatigue and decision-making stress among pedicab drivers in Dumaguete City.
•	To provide an efficient and reliable platform for commuters, especially students, to request pedicab services.
